==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slumberous
<hw>Slum"ber*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Inviting slumber; soporiferous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Pensive in the
<xex>slumberous</xex> shade.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Being in the repose of slumber; sleepy;
drowsy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His quiet and almost <qex>slumberous</qex> countenance.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slumbery</ent>⟦br⟧
